### Updates

Attributes not marked as `(Updatable)` cannot be modified after resource creation. To change these attributes, the resource must be recreated.

## Import

`terraform import` is not supported for this resource.

The `key_material` input parameters (`source_key_identifier`, `source_key_tier`,
`key_material_description`) are write-only and are not returned by the CipherTrust
Manager API. There is no way to reconstruct them from the key's current state, so
`terraform import` would leave all input parameters absent from state and cause
permanent plan diffs.

### Adopting existing key material

If an EXTERNAL AWS key already has material that was imported outside of Terraform,
you can bring that material under Terraform management by adding a
`ciphertrust_aws_key_material` resource whose `key_material` entry matches the
existing material:

```hcl
resource "ciphertrust_aws_key_material" "km" {
  aws_key_id = "<aws_key_id>"
  key_material = [{
    source_key_identifier = "<source_key_id>"
    source_key_tier       = "<source_key_tier>"
  }]
}
```

On the first `terraform apply` the provider looks up the live CipherTrust Manager
rotation history for the key. If it finds a history entry whose
`source_key_identifier` matches the value supplied, it adopts that entry rather
than importing new material bytes. After adoption, Terraform fully manages the
material - you can update `valid_to` and `key_material_description`, or delete the
material by removing the entry from `key_material`.
